<hl>
<seg id=1> Shantou Development Zone Attracts Domestic, Foreign Investors </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> XINHUA NEWS AGENCY WIRE Shantou, Dec. 20: Owing to improvements and the momentum of development in the investment climate, Shantou High Technology Development Zone has attracted the notice of both domestic and foreign investors. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Some Chinese expatriate scientists in America's "Silicon Valley" have expressed their desire to set up a high technology industry in the region, while Motorola's president for China operations and people from Ericsson have held separate talks here concerning investment projects. A Taiwanese company has expressed interest in creating a software development company in the zone as well. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> In terms of infrastructure currently in use, Shantou High Technology Development Zone has a total of 1.8 billion yuan in investment, 370,000 square meters of factory space, water, electricity, communications, bonded warehouses, etc. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Up to the beginning of November of this year there were 177 projects started in the zone altogether with a total investment value of 6.4 billion yuan.  Foreign investment accounted for 50 percent of the total, and of those enterprises seven were accorded status as "national-class high technology enterprises". </seg>
<seg id=6> This year, the whole zone's accumulated industrial output is 3.7 billion yuan.  Total income from technology, industry and trade is 4.55 billion yuan, exports add up to 127.47 million U.S. dollars, and profit-plus-tax equals 360 million yuan. </seg>
<seg id=7> During this same period, Shantou City drew up more than ten regulations and policies encouraging the establishment of technological, knowledge-intensive industries in the zone. </seg>
</p>
